        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Sorry I missed this when I put up my PR.  If you want to see what caused the second error @jjolly you can see my [in-progress PR for spack packaging](https://github.com/spack/spack/pull/46905/files) or the home-brew packaging setup.  On MacOS, a bundle can only be loaded by the equivalent of `dlopen` and not linked by `ld`.  By default luarocks and various other methods of building it build a bundle, not a dynamic library, and Neovim expects it to be a dylib.  If you switch the `-bundle` argument to `-shared -fPIC` and then also create a symlink from the `.so` to `.dylib` to work around the broken cmake (or use this patch or mine) it then works fine.\r\n\r\nAt the core this problem is because Neovim is loading a module/bundle as a dylib, which is kinda wrong, but it would be significantly more work to fix that than to do this.",
